The paper deals with the problem of sampling spectrally sparse signals below the Nyquist rate, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SP). The proposed method involves compressive sampling, which is a subfield of both cs.IT and cs.SP. The use of a bank of multipliers and lowpass filters suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the subfield of analog circuits and signal processing (cs.SI). The paper also mentions the use of digital algorithms for signal reconstruction, which could fall under the subfield of machine learning (cs.MM) or computational statistics (cs.LG).
